(** * Closure *)
(******************************************************************************)
Section section.

  Context
    `{ret_inst : Return T}
      `{Mapd_T_inst : Mapd nat T}
      `{Mapd_U_inst : Mapd nat U}
      `{Bindd_U_inst : Bindd nat T U}
      `{ToCtxset_U_inst : ToCtxset nat U}.

  Definition bound_within (gap: nat) : nat -> nat -> bool :=
    fun ix depth => ix <? depth + gap.

  Definition bound: nat -> nat -> bool :=
    bound_within 0.

  Definition cl_at_loc (gap: nat) (p: nat * nat): bool :=
    match p with
    | (depth, ix) => bound_within gap ix depth
    end.

  Definition cl_at (gap: nat) (t: U nat): Prop :=
    forall (depth ix: nat),
      (depth, ix) ‚ààd t ->
      cl_at_loc gap (depth, ix) = true.

  Definition closed (t: U nat): Prop :=
    cl_at 0 t.

End section.

Ltac bound_induction :=
  match goal with
  | |- context[bound ?ix ?n] =>
      apply (bound_ind ix n);
      let Hord := fresh "Hord" in
      let Hbound := fresh "Hbound" in
      introv Hord Hbound;
      try rewrite Hbound in *;
      try solve [lia | easy]
  end.

Ltac bound_induction_in H :=
  match type of H with
  | context[bound ?ix ?n] =>
      apply (bound_ind ix n);
      let Hord := fresh "Hord" in
      let Hbound := fresh "Hbound" in
      introv Hord Hbound;
      try rewrite Hbound in *;
      try solve [lia | easy]
  end.

 reflexivity. Qed.

Ltac simplify_lift :=
  progress repeat match goal with
    | [|- context[(+0)]] => change (+0) with (@id nat)
    | [|- context[?s S]] => change (s S) with (s (+1))
    | [|- context[S ?n + ?m]] => rewrite (plusSn n m)
    | [|- context[?n + S ?m]] => rewrite (plusnS n m)
    | [|- context[?n + 0]] => rewrite (plusnO n)
    | [|- context[0 + ?n]] => rewrite (plusOn n)
    | [|- context[(+ ?m) ‚àò (+ ?n)]] => rewrite (lift_comp m n)
    | [|- context[(?f ‚àò (+ ?m)) ‚àò (+ ?n)]] => rewrite (lift_compR m n f)
    end.

(** * Cons operation *)
(******************************************************************************)
Definition scons {X : Type} : X -> (nat -> X) -> (nat -> X)  :=
  fun new sub n => match n with
                | O => new
                | S n' => sub n'
                end.

#[local] Infix "‚ãÖ" := (scons) (at level 10).

(** * Renaming *)
(******************************************************************************)
(* Given a depth and renaming œÅ, adjust œÅ to account for the
     depth *)
Definition lift__ren: nat -> (nat -> nat) -> (nat -> nat) :=
  fun depth œÅ ix =>
    if bound ix depth
    then ix
    else let free_ix := ix - depth
         in œÅ free_ix + depth.

Definition local__ren (œÅ : nat -> nat) (p: nat * nat): nat :=
  match p with
  | (depth, ix) => lift__ren depth œÅ ix
  end.

Definition rename `{Mapd_T_inst : Mapd nat T} (œÅ : nat -> nat): T nat -> T nat :=
  mapd (T := T) (local__ren œÅ).

(* adjust a renaming to go under one binder *)
Definition up__ren (œÅ: nat -> nat): nat -> nat :=
  0 ‚ãÖ (S ‚àò œÅ).

(** * De Bruijn operations *)
(******************************************************************************)
Section ops.

  Context
    `{ret_inst : Return T}
      `{Mapd_T_inst : Mapd nat T}
      `{Bindd_U_inst : Bindd nat T U}.

  (* Given a depth and substitution œÉ, adjust œÉ to account for the
       depth *)
  Definition lift__sub: nat -> (nat -> T nat) -> (nat -> T nat) :=
    fun depth œÉ ix =>
      if ix `bound in` depth
      then ret ix
      else let free_ix := ix - depth
           in rename (+ depth) (œÉ free_ix).

  Definition local__sub (œÉ : nat -> T nat) (p: nat * nat): T nat :=
    match p with
    | (depth, ix) => lift__sub depth œÉ ix
    end.

  Definition subst (œÉ : nat -> T nat) : U nat -> U nat :=
    bindd (local__sub œÉ).

  (* adjust a substitution to go under one binder *)
  Definition up__sub (œÉ: nat -> T nat): nat -> T nat :=
    (ret 0) ‚ãÖ (rename (+1) ‚àò œÉ).

End ops.

Hord1: ix >= m + n
Hbound1: ix `bound in` (m + n) = false
rename ((+m) ‚àò (+n)) (œÉ (ix - m - n)) =
rename (+m + n) (œÉ (ix - (m + n)))

œÉ2, œÉ1: nat -> T nat

Hbound: ix `bound in` depth = false
depth', ix': nat
Hord0: ix' < depth'

Hord1: ix' < depth' + depth

  Qed.

Hord: ix >= depth
Hbound: ix `bound in` depth = false
ret (œÅ (ix - depth) + depth) =
ret (depth + œÅ (ix - depth))

    fequal; lia.
  Qed.

l, n: nat
t: U nat
œÉ: nat -> T nat
H: exists n1 n2 l1 : nat,
  (n1, l1) ‚ààd t /\
  (n2, l) ‚ààd local__sub œÉ (n1, l1) /\ n = n1 + n2
exists w1 w2 a : nat,
  (w1, a) ‚ààd t /\
  (w2, l) ‚ààd local__sub œÉ (w1, a) /\ n = w1 ‚óè w2
 assumption.
  Qed.

  Notation "'‚áë'" := up__sub.

  Notation "f ';' g" := (kc1 g f) (at level 30).
  Infix "‚ãÖ" := (scons) (at level 10).
  Notation "( + x )" := (lift x) (format "( + x )").

œÉ: nat -> T nat
k, d1, i1: nat
Hpremise: forall n depth ix : nat,
(depth, ix) ‚ààd œÉ n -> ix < depth + k
Heqb: i1 >= d1
depth, ix: nat
Hin: exists l1 : nat,
  (depth, l1) ‚ààd œÉ (i1 - d1) /\
  ix =
  (if l1 `bound in` depth
   then l1
   else depth + (+d1) (l1 - depth))
ix < depth + (k + d1)

œÉ: nat -> T nat
k: nat
Hprem: forall n depth ix : nat,
(depth, ix) ‚ààd œÉ n -> ix < depth + (k + n + 1)
depth, ix, n1, n2, i1: nat
H_in_t: (n1, i1) ‚ààd t
H_in_sig: i1 >= n1 /\
(exists l1 : nat,
   (n2, l1) ‚ààd œÉ (i1 - n1) /\
   ix =
   (if l1 `bound in` n2
    then l1
    else n2 + (+n1) (l1 - n2))) \/
i1 < n1 /\ n2 = 0 /\ ix = i1
H3: depth = n1 + n2
ix < depth + k
